comments: Brunson (NYK) wraps Siakam (TOR) with both arms , which affects his FOM during the dribble hand-off.
Anunoby (TOR) reaches in and marginal contact occurs to Quickley's (NYK) front at the start of the drive.
Barnes (TOR) initiates contact to Quickley's (NYK) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) initiates contact with VanVleet's (TOR) arm and affects VanVleet's (TOR) ability to maintain his dribble.
Barnes (TOR) slightly extends his hand to Brunson's (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs as he releases away during Brunson's rip-through.
Brunson (NYK) brings his arm toward Barnes' (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs during Barnes' drive.
VanVleet (TOR) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Brunson (NYK) brings his hand toward VanVleet's (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of VanVleet's (TOR) drive.
Anunoby (TOR) grasps and then quickly releases Randle's (NYK) jersey prior to Randle receiving the inbound pass.
Anunoby (TOR) initiates illegal contact with Randle (NYK) as he attempts to get to the pass.
Quickley (NYK) moves into Trent Jr.'s (TOR) space as he contests the jumps shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Trent Jr.'s (TOR) body after the release.
Siakam (TOR) briefly places his hands on Randle (NYK) in the backcourt and the contact is marginal.
VanVleet (TOR) slightly extends his hand to Randle's (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs as he releases the pass.
VanVleet (TOR) is moving alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs at the start of Brunson's drive.
Anunoby (TOR) is drawn into the air on the pump fake toward Brunson (NYK) and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Randle (NYK) places an arm against Trent Jr,'s (TOR) side and the contact during his driving shot attempt is marginal.
Replay review of the foul called on Barnes (TOR) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Barnes initiates contact to Brunson's (NYK) front that affects his SQBR.
Randle (NYK) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Barnes's (TOR) driving shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) and Trent Jr. (TOR) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
